 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/binary-subarrays-with-sum/description/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-03-14&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given a binary array  &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt;  and an integer  &lt;code&gt;goal&lt;/code&gt; , return &lt;em&gt;the number of non-empty &lt;strong&gt;subarrays&lt;/strong&gt; with a sum  &lt;code&gt;goal&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;subarray&lt;/strong&gt; is a contiguous part of the array.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [1,0,1,0,1], goal = 2&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 4&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Explanation:&lt;/strong&gt; The 4 subarrays are bolded and underlined below:&lt;br /&gt;
[1,0,1,0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
[1,0,1,0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
[1,0,1,0,1]&lt;br /&gt;
[1,0,1,0,1]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; nums = [0,0,0,0,0], goal = 0&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; 15&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
